OL,6,FFor Vicky Chandler, 32, it dominated
OL,7,Fher life. For three years, she would
OL,8,Fobsessively check herself for symptoms
OL,9,Fof serious illnesses. She became so
OL,10,Fconvinced that she was dying that she
OL,11,Fwould wake up every morning just
OL,12,Frelieved to still be alive.
OL,14,F"I was going to the doctor 3 to 4
OL,15,Ftimes a week. I wasn't sleeping. I was
OL,16,Flike a shell of a person," Vicky said.
OL,18,FExperts say that our preoccupation
OL,19,Fwith our health has become an acute
OL,20,Fproblem.
